TI  - Syagrus romanzoffiana (Arecaceae) Seed Utilization by Ants in a Secondary Forest in South Brazil
T2  - NEOTROPICAL ENTOMOLOGY
AB  - Ants can nest in a wide variety of substracts. This paper shows Syagrus romanzoffiana seed utilization by ants in an Atlantic secondary forest. We report 29 seeds occupied by small-bodied ants, with 27 of them showing at least two ant development stages. Although a large number of seeds were sampled, a low level of ant occupation was observed.
