T2  - REVISTA BRASILEIRA DE ORNITOLOGIA
AB  - Recent records of Platyrinchus leucoryphus (Wied, 1831) in Santa Catarina State, southern Brazil. P. leucoryphus is an Atlantic Forest Endemic vulnerable to extinction. It occurs in southeastern and southern Brazil, eastern Paraguay and northeastern Argentina, where it inhabits the understore of pristine and advanced secondary forest. This note reports recent records of P. leucoryphus in "Vale do Itajai", Santa Catarina State, Brazil.
