TI  - Supplementary description of the Brasilian palpigrade Eukoenenia janetscheki CONDE
T2  - AMAZONIANA-LIMNOLOGIA ET OECOLOGIA REGIONALIS SYSTEMAE FLUMINIS AMAZONAS
AB  - The Central Amazonian palpigrade Eukoenenia janetscheki CONDE, 1993, was established on the basis of 13 specimens, but only the adult male was fully described, with brief comments on the adult female and the juveniles of both sexes. Now, the examination of 111 individuals, all from the soil of upland primary and secondary forests, allow a much better knowledge of the species. This includes a study of the evolution of size, morphology and chaetotaxy at the three stages of the postembryonic development and sex-ratio of an isolated population (0.33 to 1.1) and the whole material at hand (0.56).
